          "author": "ianswett",
          "authorAssociation": "NONE",
          "state": "COMMENTED",
          "body": "I think linking this to what the app exposes is making this confusing.  I'd prefer to focus on what happens on the wire and how it's negotiated.",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-18T01:50:35Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-04-18T02:48:01Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 16,
              "body": "```suggestion\nThe use of the SCONE_ECHO frame is negotiated by new transport parameters\n```",
              "createdAt": "2026-04-18T01:50:35Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-04-18T02:48:01Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 18,
              "body": "```suggestion\nseparately in each direction. This negotiation is an alternate means of negotiating the\nuse of SCONE packets, in addition to scone_supported from {{SCONE}}. In\n```",
              "createdAt": "2026-04-18T01:53:00Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-04-18T02:48:01Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 20,
              "body": "I don't understand what \"In each direction,\" means?\n\nMaybe \"For a given direction,\"?\n\n",
              "createdAt": "2026-04-18T01:54:32Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-04-18T02:48:01Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 29,
              "body": "I don't think it's necessary to suppress the signal to the application layer.",
              "createdAt": "2026-04-18T01:55:36Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-04-18T02:48:01Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 28,
              "body": "```suggestion\nWhen an endpoint receives a valid SCONE packet and SCONE echo was negotiated\nin that direction, it sends a SCONE_ECHO QUIC frame in response and sends no\n```",
              "createdAt": "2026-04-18T01:56:34Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-04-18T02:48:01Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 79,
              "body": "Why?",
              "createdAt": "2026-04-18T02:43:13Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-04-18T02:48:01Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 88,
              "body": "In that case, one TP with a bool value would be better.",
              "createdAt": "2026-04-18T02:44:23Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-04-18T02:48:01Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 76,
              "body": "I think linking it to app behavior is confusing.  It's better to talk about what's on the wire.  Implementations can decide when and how to expose the SCONE signal.",
              "createdAt": "2026-04-18T02:47:17Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-04-18T02:48:01Z"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
